        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Interim government</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-12-1.jpg" alt="Interim government" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Syria <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c5yxrpkx00yo" target="_blank">established</a> a transitional government led by Mohammed al-Bashir, previously associated with the rebel administration in northwestern Syria. Bashir has been given the task of overseeing governance until March 2025. He has emphasized the need for stability and unity during this critical period.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The transitional government attempts to restore public services and institutions in areas previously affected by conflict. However, the UN and key global powers have designated <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ce313jn453zo" target="_blank">HTS</a> a terrorist organization, which makes international engagement and recognition more complicated. But many members of the HTS are trying to distance it from its past with <a href="https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/syrias-main-insurgent-group-seeks-to-distance-itself-from-past-al-qaida-ties" target="_blank">extremism</a> and carve a new future for Syria that is based on pluralism and religious tolerance.​</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">US officials have strongly encouraged <a href="https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2024-12-10/in-first-contacts-us-officials-urge-syrian-rebels-to-support-inclusive-government" target="_blank">inclusivity</a>, minority rights protection, and credible governance during this transition. Meanwhile, Damascus is showing some promising signs of <a href="https://en.protothema.gr/2024/12/11/syria-the-general-command-of-the-rebels-announces-the-lifting-of-the-curfew-in-damascus/" target="_blank">normalcy</a>, and many Syrians have already returned to their homeland. Still, the path to a peaceful and united Syria will present many challenges.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
