        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Attacks in Sudan</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-12-2.jpg" alt="Attacks in Sudan" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The situation in Sudan continues to deteriorate. On Monday, an airstrike <a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/c9wlp15400eo" target="_blank">targeted</a> a market in <a href="https://www.google.co.in/maps/place/Kabkabiya,+Sudan/@13.6475912,24.0706154,14z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x16cc03a837feae0d:0x228edba974755c58!8m2!3d13.6511432!4d24.0904246!16s%2Fg%2F1th45vtg?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI0MTIxMC4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D" target="_blank">Kabkabiya</a>, North Darfur, leaving over 100 dead. In <a href="https://www.google.co.in/maps/place/Omdurman,+Sudan/@15.6424542,32.2906706,11z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x168e8bf303b5ade3:0xffa2d3531b1ae48f!8m2!3d15.6475782!4d32.4806894!16zL20vMHBrX3k?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI0MTIxMC4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D" target="_blank">Omdurman</a>, paramilitary shelling on Tuesday <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/sudan-war-claims-over-100-more-lives-mostly-civilians/a-71017432" target="_blank">reportedly</a> killed at least 65 people, according to the governor aligned with the army. The war, ongoing since April 2023, has killed tens of thousands and displaced 12 million, with famine declared in parts of North Darfur.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The IRC <a href="https://www.rescue.org/article/top-10-crises-world-cant-ignore-2025" target="_blank">described</a> it as the worst humanitarian crisis recorded and the fastest and largest displacement crisis. Refugee camps like Zamzam face <a href="https://news.un.org/en/story/2024/12/1157726" target="_blank">starvation</a> and violence while ceasefire efforts remain stalled. The UN has renewed its call for humanitarian aid and international diplomatic intervention, focusing on achieving lasting peace to end suffering.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
