          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇰🇷 South Korea:</strong>    
          South Korea is in crisis after last week’s Martial law fiasco. Former Defense Minister Kim Yong-hyun, who is currently detained over his alleged role, attempted suicide while in custody but survived. The <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/10/asia/south-korea-defense-minister-suicide-attempt-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">incident</a> occurred in the bathroom, and Kim Yong-hyun gave up on the attempt when the corrections officer came in. The officers have moved him to isolation and confirmed that he has no health issues. Three top military commanders have been suspended for their roles in Yoon’s imposition of martial law. Yoon is facing treason allegations and a second impeachment attempt; He is under investigation alongside top officials. Calls for his resignation continue, including from his own People Power Party.</p>
        </mj-text>
