          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇸🇾 Syria:</strong>   
          The collapse of Bashar al-Assad’s regime in Syria has prompted Israel to launch extensive military strikes, including <a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2024/12/10/barrage-of-israeli-attacks-destroys-important-military-sites-in-syria" target="_blank">480 airstrikes</a> and the deployment of ground troops beyond the demilitarized buffer zone for the first time in 50 years. Israel used key military sites, including airfields, missiles, and naval facilities, as targets. Israel aims to neutralize strategic weapons and prevent them from falling into the hands of extremist groups. While Israeli officials frame their actions as necessary for national security, particularly along the Golan Heights, several Arab states have accused Israel of exploiting the instability to expand its territory.</p>
        </mj-text>
